      <h2 style="text-align:center;">Last Notes:</h2>
      <p>The role of the submitted coursework in Oxbridge admissions varies. Some colleges use it only to consider who to invite for interview. Others use it to form the basis of the interview. Due to this, your written coursework should be on a topic that you are ready to discuss with an expert. This means having read widely enough and thought deeply enough on it so that you can hold an intellectual conversation. There is no real preference between writing coursework from scratch or using one from your existing schoolwork. So long as your work shows the four skills above and is on a topic you are passionate and knowledgeable about, you will do well.</p>
